abstract: In the waning hours before New Hampshire’s first-in-the-nation primary voting begins, Democratic presidential candidates took varied approaches to the expectations game Monday as they look to advance deeper into what could be an extended nominating fight.
snippet: In the waning hours before New Hampshire’s first-in-the-nation primary voting begins, Democratic presidential candidates took varied approaches to the expectations game Monday as they look to advance deeper into what could be an extended nominatin...
lead_paragraph: ROCHESTER, N.H. — In the waning hours before New Hampshire’s first-in-the-nation primary voting begins, Democratic presidential candidates took varied approaches to the expectations game Monday as they look to advance deeper into what could be an extended nominating fight.
headline_main: How Crucial Is New Hampshire Win? It Depends on Whom You Ask
headline_print_headline: How Crucial Is New Hampshire Win? It Depends on Whom You Ask

abstract: A few states will use it in their 2020 primaries, and some cities have been using it for years. Proponents say it could make politics more civil. Critics say it could hurt turnout.

lead_paragraph: Presidential election years always raise big questions about the way we vote, in part because the process can get kind of messy.

abstract: New Hampshire voters are poised Tuesday to re-order the field of Democratic presidential candidates. But as important, they will also send a message about what kind of change they want their party to stand for to challenge President Donald Trump.
snippet: New Hampshire voters are poised Tuesday to re-order the field of Democratic presidential candidates. But as important, they will also send a message about what kind of change they want their party to stand for to challenge President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: HANOVER, N.H. — New Hampshire voters are poised Tuesday to re-order the field of Democratic presidential candidates. But as important, they will also send a message about what kind of change they want their party to stand for to challenge President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Revolution or Realism? NH Tests Democrats' Call for Change

abstract: A day before New Hampshire votes in its Democratic presidential primary, Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg sought on Monday to build on their strength as front-runners in an up-for-grabs race as an energized Senator Amy Klobuchar gained ground.

lead_paragraph: KEENE/NASHUA, N.H. — A day before New Hampshire votes in its Democratic presidential primary, Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg sought on Monday to build on their strength as front-runners in an up-for-grabs race as an energized Senator Amy Klobuchar gained ground.

abstract: Hatton Garden has long been known as the center of Britain’s jewelry trade. Now, independent makers and small businesses are trying to ensure it keeps that role.
snippet: Hatton Garden has long been known as the center of Britain’s jewelry trade. Now, independent makers and small businesses are trying to ensure it keeps that role.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — Barry Coumbe was describing operations at F. Sinclair, his polishing business in Hatton Garden, when he recalled that wheelbarrows were piled high with its commemorative gold ingots for Queen Elizabeth’s 1977 Silver Jubilee to move them between the company’s two workshops.
